,"1250":"1250","1281":"1281","1270":"1270","1316":"1316","1302":"1302","1246":"1246","1213":"1213","1323":"1323","1366":"1366","1211":"1211","Abt 1280":"circa 1280","Walcott, Norfolk, , England":"Walcott, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Walcott, Norfolk, England":"Walcott, Norfolk, England","Taunton, Somerset, , England":"Taunton, Somerset, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1246–1366":"1246–1366","1270–1323":"1270–1323","1250–Female":"1250–Deceased","1281–1382":"1281–1382","1316–1383":"1316–1383","1211–1302":"1211–1302","1213–Female":"1213–Deceased","ABT 1323":"about 1323","1383":"1383","1382":"1382","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","1270":"1270","1316":"1316","1302":"1302","1246":"1246","1213":"1213","1323":"1323","1366":"1366","1211":"1211","Abt 1280":"about 1280","Walcott, Norfolk, , England":"Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Walcott, Norfolk, England":"Walcott, Norfolk, England","Taunton, Somerset, , England":"Taunton, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wolcott","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Devon and Surrey): habitational name from Wollacott in Thrushelton (Devon), named from the Old English personal name <i>Wulfnōth</i> + <i>cot</i> ‘cottage, hut, shelter’. This form of the surname is now rare in Britain.","History: Henry Wolcott (1578–1655), clothier, came from Tolland, Somerset, England, and settled in Windsor, CT, in 1636. His grandson Roger (1679–1767) was colonial governor of CT; his great-grandson Oliver (1726–1797) was a signer of the Declaration of Independence."],"variants":[{"name":"Woolcott","meanings":["English: variant of   Wolcott  ."]},{"name":"Woolcock","meanings":["English (Cornwall): probably a variant of   Wolcott  ."]}]},{"name":"Philip","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Philip Wolcott was born in 1246, in Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Roger Wolcott, was 35 and his mother, Mrs. Roger Walcot, was 33. He married Julian Herle about 1280, in Walcott, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1366, in Taunton, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 120."},"et":{"1246–1366":"1246–1366","1270–1323":"1270–1323","1250–Female":"1250–Surnud","1281–1382":"1281–1382","1316–1383":"1316–1383","1211–1302":"1211–1302","1213–Female":"1213–Surnud","ABT 1323":"umbes 1323","1383":"1383","1382":"1382","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","1270":"1270","1316":"1316","1302":"1302","1246":"1246","1213":"1213","1323":"1323","1366":"1366","1211":"1211","Abt 1280":"umbes 1280","Walcott, Norfolk, , England":"Walcott, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Walcott, Norfolk, England":"Walcott, Norfolk, England","Taunton, Somerset, , England":"Taunton, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1246–1366":"1246–1366","1270–1323":"1270–1323","1250–Female":"1250–Kuollut","1281–1382":"1281–1382","1316–1383":"1316–1383","1211–1302":"1211–1302","1213–Female":"1213–Kuollut","ABT 1323":"noin 1323","1383":"1383","1382":"1382","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","1270":"1270","1316":"1316","1302":"1302","1246":"1246","1213":"1213","1323":"1323","1366":"1366","1211":"1211","Abt 1280":"noin 1280","Walcott, Norfolk, , England":"Walcott, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Walcott, Norfolk, England":"Walcott, Norfolk, England","Taunton, Somerset, , England":"Taunton, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"12